Description: 501(C)3 non Profit for School Supplies for underprivileged children from K-12 In the USA
Headquarters Regions: Greater Los Angeles Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: Who We Help “When families have to choose between food and school supplies, your support enables me to reduce some of their worry. You allow us to provide tools to  further success, encourage expression, and create an equal education for all students.” For every purchased box one will be donated to a Nigerian Student in Africa.   Our funding priority is school supplies for youth education up to college, specifically in the following areas  STEM. The emphasis is on increasing student achievement in STEM  science, technology, engineering, mathematics, and literacy at the end of the school year a  college scholarship will be giving to One Student in America and one student in Nigeria.   We created Mitch School Box Club as a non-for-profit so that not only is it a one-stop shopping portal for your back-to-school supplies and educational enrichment supplies, but a means by which WE collectively can help those children who need most support.  It will be donated to a disadvantaged child in your community.   ​ Our Focus Mitch School Box Club Foundation tackles critical problems primarily affecting the United States and Nigeria Africa for the  poor and disadvantaged, and supports strong and effective partner organizations to do the same. We believe that good stewardship means maximizing our resources, including grant funding and staff time, while building strong partnerships based on trust.  Students When families can barely afford rent and groceries, school supplies just can’t be a priority. For these students struggling with extreme poverty, and to provide distressed communities and disadvantaged students we can offer school supplies. We serve kids at schools where at least 70% of students are enrolled in the federal free or reduced lunch program. We do this through our National Network of Resource Centers and our School Ready Supplies program.  Teachers On average, teachers spend $578 per year from their own pockets on school supplies for their classrooms. That’s why we offer 40 Resource Centers across the country where teachers can go to obtain free school supplies. We also offer Teacher Supply Boxes provide successful applicants with two boxes containing roughly $500 in the most essential school supplies — from notebooks and markers to pens and glue. ​ Education A solid foundation in education is key to success later in life. Your donations fund teachers, books and extracurricular activities to help get youngsters off to the right start. This will also help us support every School in America with a strong S.T.E.M Program in there school which will also help our overseas schools in Nigeria. Community Community is the family that goes beyond family. It is the people and places that we come in contact with each and every day. When we strengthen communities, we strengthen individuals.

The US Olympic Committee was looking for a way to help schedule their various events using the burgeoning new field of computer technology. Description: The OpenLDAP Foundation is a not-for-profit corporation with a charter to promote open-source LDAP development.
Headquarters Regions: San Francisco Bay Area, Silicon Valley, West Coast
Full Description: The OpenLDAP Foundation is a not-for-profit corporation with a charter to promote open-source LDAP development. The foundation is funded by contributions from sponsors and contributors. The foundation coordinates the activities of the OpenLDAP Project that it established in August 1998. The project is a collaborative effort to develop an open-source LDAP suite of applications and development tools. OpenLDAP Software is a suite of directory software developed by the internet community. It is an open-source implementation of the Lightweight Directory Access Protocol. The suite includes slapd (stand-alone LDAP daemon); libraries implementing the LDAP protocol; and utilities, tools, and sample clients.
